🛠️ Step-by-Step: Create .venv in VS Code
Step 1 — Create the project folder

Go to your Desktop

Create a new folder named:Learning_Python
---
Step 2 — Open the folder in VS Code

Open VS Code

Click File → Open Folder

Select Learning_Python

Open the Terminal:

Menu → Terminal → New Terminal

---

Step 3 — Create the virtual environment

In the terminal, run: py -m venv .venv
This creates the .venv folder inside your project.

---

Step 4 — Activate .venv
PowerShell
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

When activated, you will see:
(.venv)

---

Step 5 — Select .venv in VS Code (VERY IMPORTANT)

Press:Ctrl + Shift + P
Type:Python: Select Interpreter
Choose the interpreter that includes:.venv

Now VS Code uses your project’s Python environment.

---

📦 Installing Libraries

Once .venv is active:
pip install requests
Save dependencies:pip freeze > requirements.txt

---

🚫 Important: .gitignore
Create a .gitignore file and add:
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env
This keeps your repository clean.

